I doubt there would be a difference. Pinging google.com **through** a specific server shows that the server you're testing works. Google.com is actually a better option since it'll show more accurate results, as it is a widely used website.

When you click on "Test servers real delay" or Ctrl + R, V2RayN runs a ping tested from your connection through the server, not directly from your device. In case you want to get a better result, maybe you can try speed test instead, it'll show if the server is fast enough or not (Shortcut is Ctrl + T).

